{
  "texts": [
    "The Facial Action Coding Method (FACS) is a classification system for facial impressions based on facial affectation.",
    "It was first proposed in 1978 by Ekman and Friesen, and it was modified in 2002 by Hager (Lakshminarayanan et al. 2017).",
    "Several studies depend on face images.",
    "For example (Wells et al. 2016), R. Sadik et al.",
    "utilize transfer learning in emotion recognition."
  ]
}